Way back when, when the focus item effects were new and not totally understood, I spent hours testing each effect.  To make a long story short, without SE I was able to cast 17 pets, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">with</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> SE I could cast 19.  That suggests around 10% savings for <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Summoning Efficiency</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  If SE had been 25% mana savings, then I would have been able to cast 22 pets, not 19.<br>
<br>
