<br>
There is one thing you did not take into consideration, and that is regardless of your mana savings, a 200 mana spell will NOT cast unless you have 200 mana to spend.  If it costs you 170 mana or less, tough luck.... you need 200 mana in your current pool in order to cast it.  The mana check is made BEFORE any effects are taken into consideration.  This would add 1 or 2 casts to your tally.  Assuming 2 more casts before truly OOM, that would put you at 21 pets, not 19.  This would put you at the margin of error for efficiency percentages. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2528<br> <font color=#333333>(12/27/02 3:38:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=474.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet canni breakdown - for a conj/scm3 magician</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This would add 1 or 2 casts to your tally.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->This would add at most one cast to the tally.  Even if it were 20 casts, that would still be no more than 15% savings.  I repeated the experiment multiple times, and there was no variation at all.<br>
