<br>
scm 3 = 15%<br>
Spec Conj = 10%<br>
Summ Eff = 25%<br>
<br>
Total = 50%<br>
<br>
If you for a moment assume that SE is indeed 25%, it would add 2 casts to the tally, and put you at the margin of error for efficiency percentages.  If you assume that SE is 15%, then you will only get one more cast, and will yield about 15%.  If you assume SE is 10%, you will also be running about 15%.  So, there is a margin of error, and it depends exactly on the number we are trying to figure out.<br>
<br>
My recommendation is to get Spell Casting Expertise 1 and try your experiment on the level 4 pets.  The more pets you can cast, the more accurate the percentages will become.<br>
<br>
My personal difficulty with these experiments is trying to match my mana pool exactly with and without the Enshrouded Veil.  Without being able to match it exactly, the experiment is prone to at least some degree of error.  Also fizzles are an unknown, so you have to eliminate them entirely. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=balanzsonofanz>Balanz son of Anz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Abuser of EZCodes</span><br>  Posts: 2536<br> <font color=#333333>(12/27/02 5:17:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=474.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Pet canni breakdown - for a conj/scm3 magician</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>try your experiment on the level 4 pets.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->I chose the 200 mana pets because the number of casts, 20ish, is sufficient, but the cost is large compared to the other errors that might be introduced, for example not taking the same amount of time to cast each pet and getting more mana generation than expected.<br>
